py-msbuild-extractor
====================

This repository packages and redistributes third-party software. The wheel it
produces bundles a compiled, self-contained win-x64 build of the project listed
below (plus one supporting native library); this NOTICE and the upstream
license travel with that redistribution.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
msbuild-extractor-sample
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source:             https://github.com/microsoft/msbuild-extractor-sample
Vendored at commit: 4ae6d2f344424a4eb408d88c614b1a73a7e48045 (tag v0.2.0)
License:            MIT

The upstream MIT license text is reproduced below. It is also shipped inside the
wheel at py_msbuild_extractor/licenses/msbuild-extractor-sample-LICENSE.txt and
retained in the vendored submodule at vendor/msbuild-extractor-sample/LICENSE.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
hostfxr.dll (.NET runtime host resolver)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source:  https://github.com/dotnet/runtime
License: MIT

`build.ps1` copies hostfxr.dll from the .NET SDK used to build the wheel and
ships it as bin/hostfxr.dll, next to msbuild-extractor.exe. It is required for
Microsoft.Build.Locator's .NET SDK discovery (see
packaging/python-wheel/patches/README.md for details); the self-contained
single-file publish of msbuild-extractor-sample does not otherwise produce a
loadable copy of it. The dotnet/runtime MIT license text is the same as the
one reproduced below.

